Valuation Assumptions  Stock Options and SARs
 
Cablevision calculates the fair value of each option award on the date of grant and for each SAR on the date of grant and at the end of each reporting period using the Black-Scholes option pricing model. Cablevision's computation of expected life was determined based on historical experience of similar awards, giving consideration to the contractual terms of the share-based awards and vesting schedules or the simplified method (the average of the vesting period and option term), if applicable. The interest rate for periods within the contractual life of the share-based award is based on interest yields for U.S. Treasury instruments in effect at the time of grant and as of December 31, 2010, 2009 and 2008 for SARs. Cablevision's computation of expected volatility is based on historical volatility of its common stock.
 
