     On June 30, 2010, AMC Networks' amended and restated by-laws became effective. The amended and restated by-laws have been filed as Exhibit 99.5 to this Form 8-K.
     On June 30, 2011, Cablevision effected the distribution of all of AMC's outstanding common stock. In the Distribution, each holder of Cablevision NY Group Class A Common Stock of record as of the close of business, New York City time, on June 16, 2011 (the "record date"), received one share of AMC Class A Common Stock for every four shares of Cablevision NY Group Class A Common Stock held on the record date. Each record holder of Cablevision NY Group Class B Common Stock received one share of AMC Class B Common Stock for every four shares of Cablevision NY Group Class B Common Stock held on the record date. In the Distribution, an aggregate of 57,813,256.75 shares of AMC Class A Common Stock and 13,534,418.25 shares of AMC Class B Common Stock were issued.
